OL,6,F"Eventhough the charity's been running
OL,7,Ffor 30 years, very few people know
OL,8,Fthat we're out there. They just
OL,9,Fpresume that we're part of the
OL,10,Fambulance service. But no, everyone
OL,11,Fwho's part of MEDSERVE is a
OL,12,Fvolunteer."JBack in Newport, Chris and
OL,13,FRondine want to shine a spotlight on
OL,14,Fthose volunteers.JRondine said: "You
OL,15,Fknow there are huge pressures across
OL,16,Fthe field in health and social care.
OL,18,F"They're such an invaluable resource
OL,19,Fand we've got to make sure they get
OL,20,Fthe funding they need to continue."
